<p>Hello Abe Estos,</p>
<p>Welcome to the site! The SCP Wiki is a great place for writers of all levels, so you've come to the right spot.</p>
<p>For advice in critiquing, I recommend checking out our critique threads here in the forums, and looking at the posts stickied at the top of each list. Here you'll find all the relevant info in regards to giving feedback, and all relevant rules to follow.</p>
<p>For advice in writing, I'm going to leave you with my writer's resources. It contains links to all the places to get started/what to read first/ect. Do keep in mind there is no rush to contribute, so if you're not quite ready to, don't! Reading, exploring the site, and seeing what all you like are also wonderful places to start.</p>
<p>If you have any questions/concerns, feel free to reach out, otherwise, enjoy your time here!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+A&nbsp;gift&nbsp;of&nbsp;resources&nbsp;just&nbsp;for&nbsp;you</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-Hope&nbsp;this&nbsp;helps!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Maybe you've already seen these before, maybe you haven't, but hopefully something here is of use to you. Of course, if you have any questions, feel free to reach out!</p>
<p>First off, there are some required readings for all site authors. Consider giving them a read, as well as all the other helpful guides on this <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/guide-hub">Guide Hub.</a> The more familiar you are with the processes that take place on the Site, the better your chances of success are!</p>
<p>Now that that's done - Got an idea? Or maybe a few? You can create a <a href="http://scp-sandbox-3.wikidot.com/">Sandbox</a> page to store all your ideas and drafts in an orderly fashion.</p>
<p>Okay, but maybe you're not sure if your concept is ready to be fleshed out, or perhaps it just needs some heavy refinement. If that's the case, you can run things by the community in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-89000/help:ideas-and-brainstorming">Ideas and Brainstorming</a> forum.</p>
<p>Once you believe you have a solid draft, you can go ahead and make a thread in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-50864/help:drafts-and-critiques">Drafts and Critiques</a> forum. Keep in mind though you should check the stickied posts first on how best to use each of the forums.</p>
<p>Best of luck writing!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

